 {"id":"bd-3utu","title":"Integrate reactor into RuntimeState","description":"# Task: Integrate Reactor into RuntimeState

## What

Add the IoDriver to RuntimeState and wire up the runtime's main loop to call IoDriver::turn().

## Location

`src/runtime/state.rs` (existing file)

## Current State

RuntimeState holds:
```rust
pub struct RuntimeState {
    regions: Arena<RegionRecord>,
    tasks: Arena<TaskRecord>,
    obligations: Arena<ObligationRecord>,
    now: Time,
    stored_tasks: HashMap<TaskId, StoredTask>,
    trace: TraceBuffer,
    // ... no I/O driver yet
}
```

## Design

Add IoDriver as optional (allows Lab runtime without real I/O):

```rust
pub struct RuntimeState {
    // ... existing fields ...

    /// I/O driver for reactor integration (None in pure Lab mode)
    io_driver: Option<IoDriver>,
}

impl RuntimeState {
    /// Create runtime with a real reactor for production use.
    pub fn with_reactor(reactor: Arc<dyn Reactor>) -> Self {
        Self {
            // ... existing initialization ...
            io_driver: Some(IoDriver::new(reactor)),
        }
    }

    /// Create runtime without reactor (Lab mode with virtual I/O).
    pub fn without_reactor() -> Self {
        Self {
            // ... existing initialization ...
            io_driver: None,
        }
    }

    /// Access the I/O driver (if present).
    pub fn io_driver(&self) -> Option<&IoDriver> {
        self.io_driver.as_ref()
    }

    pub fn io_driver_mut(&mut self) -> Option<&mut IoDriver> {
        self.io_driver.as_mut()
    }
}
```

## Main Loop Integration

Modify the runtime's execution loop:

```rust
// Before (Phase 0):
loop {
    // Just run tasks, no I/O wait
    while let Some(task) = scheduler.pop() {
        task.poll();
    }
    // Busy-loop if tasks pending
}

// After (Phase 2):
loop {
    // 1. Run ready tasks
    while let Some(task) = scheduler.pop() {
        task.poll();
    }

    // 2. Check if quiescent
    if scheduler.is_empty() && self.io_driver.map_or(true, |d| d.is_empty()) {
        break; // All done
    }

    // 3. Process timers, compute next deadline
    let timeout = self.timer_wheel.next_deadline().map(|d| d - self.now);

    // 4. Wait for I/O events (or timeout)
    if let Some(driver) = &mut self.io_driver {
        driver.turn(timeout)?;
    }
}
```

## Quiescence Condition

For region close to work correctly:
- No running tasks
- No pending timers
- No registered I/O sources with unfired events

## Capability Context (Cx) Integration

Add IoCap to Cx for registering I/O:

```rust
impl Cx {
    /// Register an I/O source (requires IoCap).
    pub fn register_io(
        &self,
        source: &dyn Source,
        interest: Interest,
    ) -> io::Result<Registration> {
        let waker = self.waker();
        self.runtime.io_driver_mut()
            .ok_or_else(|| io::Error::new(io::ErrorKind::Unsupported, "no reactor"))?
            .register(source, interest, waker)
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] IoDriver added to RuntimeState (optional)
- [ ] with_reactor() / without_reactor() constructors
- [ ] Main loop calls turn() when I/O driver present
- [ ] Quiescence check includes I/O driver state
- [ ] Cx gains register_io() method
- [ ] Existing tests pass (Lab mode without reactor)
- [ ] Integration test with real reactor","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"OpusNova","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T05:41:39.644040155Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-18T17:49:10.172734491Z","closed_at":"2026-01-18T17:49:10.172734491Z","close_reason":"Implemented IoDriver integration with constructors, accessors, and quiescence check","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3utu","depends_on_id":"bd-tk79","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-03T00:01:52Z","created_by":"import"}]}
